Implemented the Armstrong number check in `armstrong-numbers.js` using BigInt to handle extremely large numbers (up to 39 digits), and unskipped all the `xtest` cases in `armstrong-numbers.spec.js` so they run as regular tests.

Implementation:
```js
export const isArmstrongNumber = (number) => {
  const numStr = number.toString();
  const digits = numStr.length;
  let sum = 0n;
  for (let i = 0; i < digits; i++) {
    const digit = BigInt(numStr[i]);
    sum += digit ** BigInt(digits);
  }
  return sum === BigInt(number);
};
```

